==English==
===Noun===
#The action of [[slander]]ing a person without that person's knowledge.
#*'''1303''' No custummable bakbytyng God.... &mdash; Robert Manning of Brune, ''Handlyng synne''
#*'''1862''' Not given to backbiting. &mdash; Anthony Trollope, ''Orley Farm''

===Adjective===
#Describes a person who slanders or speaks badly of a person without that person's knowledge.
#*'''1580''' Backbiting talk that flattering blabs know wily how to blenge. &mdash; Thomas Tusser, ''A hundreth good pointes of husbandrie''
#*'''1873''' Am I to have a backbiting wife? &mdash; Rhoda Broughton, ''Nancy''

